# What is Reverse Image Search?

Reverse Image Search is an OSINT technique that allows users to search the internet using an image instead of text.
Instead of entering keywords into a search engine, users upload an image or provide its URL. 
The search engine analyzes the visual features of the image and compares them against billions of indexed images available on the internet.

This technique helps answer important investigative questions such as:

* Where did this image originally come from?
* Has this image been used elsewhere online?
* Is the image authentic or manipulated?
* Can the location shown in the image be identified?
* Has this image been shared with misleading information?

Reverse Image Search focuses on visual content rather than textual information, making it one of the most valuable OSINT techniques for image verification.

